  "INTERPRETATION": "CLEAN handles are safe in both architectures. The relay's value is on tcr_dependent handles: it converts 'safe only if the TCR is near-perfect (beta<=0.02/pf)' into 'safe if the TCR is decent (beta<=0.17/pf)'. Whether a given handle clears even the relaxed bar is the RUNG-12 structural question -- but the relay widens the target phase space ~8.6x."
